title: West Harbour ferry saved from sinking
text:
West Harbour ferry saved from sinking 
Wednesday 2 Sep 2015 12:34 p.m. 
Fire crews were called to pump water from the ferry (Photo: SNPA/Daniel Hines) 
By 3 News online staff 
A small ferry in Auckland's West Harbour has been pulled to dry land after it started to sink at West Park Marina this morning. 
One fire crew was called to help pump water from the vessel, which is operated by Belaire Ferries. 
A Fire Service communications manager said the boat has been stabilised and pulled to land. 
It's unclear how the boat came to take on water. 
3 News
